<TITLE> Suazo nets twice, honours Chile earthquake victims </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MADRID, Feb 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Chile striker Humberto Suazo struck twice to give Real Zaragoza a 2-0 win at Getafe in La Liga on Saturday and sent a message of support to his countrymen following the deadly earthquake there. The 28-year-old pounced on a defensive error to round Getafe goalkeeper Jordi Codina and put Zaragoza ahead in the third minute and lifted his shirt to reveal a vest with "Fuerza Chile" (Chile be strong) written across it. The shaven-headed forward, who netted 10 goals in Chile's successful World Cup qualifying campaign, then showed the vest again after powering in a 20th-minute header to double Zaragoza's advantage. A huge magnitude-8.8 earthquake shook Chile early on Saturday, killing at least 147 people, knocking down homes and hospitals, and triggering a tsunami in the Pacific. Suazo's gesture recalled one by Cristiano Ronaldo last weekend when the Real Madrid forward revealed a vest with "Madeira" written on it after scoring against Villarreal. The Portuguese international's native island had been struck by floods which left at least 42 dead. Suazo missed a chance to complete his hat-trick late on and had to leave the pitch after appearing to damage his left hamst
